    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">步子</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">步</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>WALK FORWARDso as to RAISE A FOOT AND THEN PUT it DOWN AGAIN; AND DISTANCE TYPICALLY COVERED by this ACT.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general word for the length of two steps is bù 步.</p>
<p>2. Kuǐ 跬／蹞／頃 refers to the ground covered by a single step, lifting only one foot.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
